<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="G2" checkit-title="Volume">
    <statement>
        <p> A rectangular prism stands with it's longest side vertical and a pyramid is attached cleanly to the bottom of the rectangular prism. The dimensions of the shape are as follows: the rectangular prism has height 11, length 3, and width 8, and the pyramid has altitude 7, where everything is measured in meters.
            <ol>
                <li>Sketch a drawing of this situation to the best of your ability.</li>
                <li>Find the total volume of this shape.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            The volume is <m>V \approx 320.0</m> <m>m^3</m>. This was computed using the formula <m>V = \ell w h_1 + \frac{1}{3}\ell w h_2</m>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
